I am 52 and very top heavy and in May, I asked my doctor why my breasts seem to be "growing" and I was told it's because I put on weight (mind you, my medical records show I had been gaining and losing the same 5-10 pounds for at least 2 years.) To appease me, I was sent for my annual mammogram screening. The amount of time that passed between the order for the test being placed to the time it took to finally get me on the schedule was 2 months (I was told the delay was because of COVID), but in that time, a lump appeared almost in the center of my chest. Initially, I was told that because it showed up so quickly, it was probably just a cyst. Well, I demanded to bypass additional tests and partial biopsies and went straight for surgical removal of the lump and I'm glad I did. It wasn't a cyst; it was a fast growing tumor (that wasn't there in January) and I have been diagnosed with triple negative breast cancer. This coming week, I will get my surgery and my chemo on the schedule and I am ready to fight with every ounce of strength God has given me. My point...if you feel something is wrong, don't let your doctors downplay your concerns. Get screened, demand action and get everyone on the same page with your health.

Three people get stranded on an island. They think they're alone but get caught by  indigenous people. The indigenous people tell the three men that the only way they will permit the men to survive is if the men go into the woods and bring back 10 pieces of fruit.The men say, ok that doesn't sound too bad. They run into the woods for a while and eventually the first man comes back. He has his arms full with apples. He drops on the sand and says, "Here's your apples, please let me live!" The tribespeople say that there are two parts to survival. The man is told he must put all 10 pieces of fruit up his bum without making any facial expressions or sounds. The man looks horrified, but in the name of survival, he begins. 1...2... and he bursts out crying in pain. The tribespeople kill him on the spot.A little later the second man comes running up. He has 10 grapes in his hands, and after hearing what he must do, he begins putting them in his bum. 1...2...3...4...5...6...7...8...9... and he BURSTS out laughing. He is killed on the spot.Now up in heaven, the first man sees the second man and goes "Hey, I was watching you, why didn't you just control yourself for a few more seconds so you could get that last grape and live??" The second man replies, "I couldn't help myself, I saw the third guy running over with pineapples."
